description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a registered nurse looking to join an award winning team at Sheffield Teaching Hospitals? Are you forward thinking, a team player and keen to develop?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Medicine and Pharmacy Services (MAPs) includes the directorates of Respiratory Medicine, Diabetes and Endocrine and Gastroenterology &amp; Hepatology. Rotational programmes are available and these offer fantastic scope to develop your skills, interests and specialty knowledge with support from excellent, experienced leaders and a dedicated Clinical Educator team at one of the largest teaching trusts in the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are also opportunities for registered nurses to be supported to transition back into the hospital setting, including a programme which MAPS supports in collaboration with NHSP.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please only apply if you do hold a NMC PIN or have completed the (if required) OSCE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Specialities and Wards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Respiratory&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have 6 Respiratory wards covering Respiratory conditions including Asthma, COPD, Cystic Fibrosis, Lung Cancer, Mesothelioma, Pneumonia, Pulmonary Fibrosis, Respiratory infections, Sleep Apnoea and Tuberculosis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Brearley wards are general Respiratory with Brearley 4 having a Respiratory Support Unit which has 4 high dependency beds caring for patients requiring non-invasive ventilation. Our Cystic Fibrosis ward is a purpose built unit which provides specialist medical and nursing care in an environment which meets the needs of this patient group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;M2 is our Pulmonary Hypertension Unit which has 16 inpatient beds, with a day case, Respiratory function unit, an echocardiography suite and pulmonary exercise lab.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gastroenterology and Hepatology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our patients have conditions of the gastrointestinal tract and include Crohns, Colitis, Cancer and gastrointestinal bleeding. We also care for patients with Liver disease and this includes patients with alcohol issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D&amp;E&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Diabetes &amp; Endocrine teams provide specialist care to patients with multiple and complex diabetes and endocrinology disorders and includes specialist support, education and training to patients with long term conditions such as heart failure, renal impairment. We also provide specialist inpatient treatment for patients with complex eating disorders, working closely with inpatient and community specialist medical and nursing mental health teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endoscopy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A major part of our service&#39;s work is the provision of endoscopic services, both at the Northern and Central campus including the Clinical Investigation Unit (CIU) Ward P1 at Central campus. Services include upper gastrointestinal endoscopy, sigmoidoscopy, colonoscopy and therapeutic procedures such as treatment of bleeding sources and oesophageal dilatation. We also provide a service for endoscopic ultrasound and hepatobiliary endoscopic ultrasound.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rotation posts &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A rotation is a unique way to try different wards within specialities but with the structure and learning in place with a security of a guaranteed post on completion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Respiratory Rotation includes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 months on the Cystic Fibrosis Unit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 months on M2&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;9 months on Brearley 4&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;9 months on Brearley 1, 2 or 3&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The MAPS Rotation includes;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respiratory Brearley 1, 2,3 and 4, Cystic Fibrosis and M2&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gastroenterology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diabetes and Endocrinology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please state on your application form what post you are interested in applying for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in expanding your knowledge and joining one of our teams, we would love to hear from you. The Medicine and Pharmacy Care group (MAPS) was recently highly commended for their passion to drive nursing forward. Look for us on twitter #teamMAPS #brilliantplacetowork&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;****************************************************************************&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For those who are currently employed by the Trust as a Staff Nurse, you should instead apply through the Staff Nurse Transfer process via your line manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a Newly Qualified applicant and are due to qualify before end of June 2021, you can apply via this advert. Please specify what month and year you are due to qualify. Please also specify the hours and list the three wards/areas you would prefer to work within.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are due to qualify from July - December 2021, please apply on our specific Newly Qualified Nurse advert which will be live on NHS jobs early next year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;****************************************************************************&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
